Ten thousand of music, PE and art teachers will be trained for rural primary schools in Jiangxi within 3 years - Xinhuanet Message from Nanchang of the Xinhua News Agency on May 22 (journalists: Chen Yushan): According to Ministry of Education of Jiangxi, in order to strengthen the guarantee for subject teachers and realize balanced development of compulsory education in rural areas, Jiangxi planned to train 1 music teacher, 1 art teacher and 1 PE teacher for each primary school in rural areas of the whole province (villages, towns and below) since 2016, totally 10 thousand teachers. It is understood that the training objects are teachers of other subjects under 45 years old with basic knowledge or talent of music, art and PE in rural primary schools in Jiangxi and can work as music, art or PE teachers at the same time. They can master basic knowledge and teaching skills about music, PE and art after training, and can update teaching ideas and concepts, master modern teaching methods, improve subject teaching ability, activity design ability, campus cultural ability and self-development ability, so as to construct the team of music, PE and art teachers good at many subjects and expert in one, to relieve the problem of lack of music, PE and art teachers in rural primary schools. In order to ensure training quality and effect, Jiangxi plans to train 1 music teacher, 1 art teacher and 1 PE teacher for each primary school in 100 counties (cities and districts) in Jiangxi, with totally 300 trainers, to comprehensively improve their teaching demonstration leading ability, teaching research activity design and organization ability, training ability, network research workshop construction ability, playing roles in teaching, demonstration, guiding and supervising.
